<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1729,2029]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,339,1845,1871]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Etymology</emphasis>
. Dedicated to Prof. Dr. Augusto Vigna Taglianti for his important contributions to the faunistics and systematics of the Italian and European 
<taxonomicName box="[789,912,1884,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carabidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1729,2029]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,151,410]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,268,1923,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Notes</emphasis>
. In 
<number box="[318,380,1923,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="1965.0">1965</number>
, Magistretti cited 
<taxonomicName box="[601,872,1923,1948]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dalmatinus">
<emphasis box="[601,872,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Platyderus dalmatinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Gargano Mt. as listing three records: “Monte Sant’Angelo”, “Montenero”, and “Foresta Umbra” (
<bibRefCitation author="Magistretti" box="[856,1118,1962,1991]" pageId="8" pageNumber="51" refString="Magistretti, M. (1965) Fauna d'Italia VIII. Coleoptera, Cicindelidae, Carabidae, Catalogo topografico. Calderini, Bologna, xv + 512 pp." type="book" year="1965">
Magistretti 
<number box="[993,1056,1965,1991]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="1965.0">1965</number>
: 
<number box="[1067,1110,1965,1991]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="421.0">421</number>
<number box="[1110,1118,1962,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). For this reason, one male and two females of the typical 
<taxonomicName box="[520,682,2003,2029]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dalmatinus">
<emphasis box="[520,535,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[551,682,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">dalmatinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[756,900,2003,2029]" name="Serbia" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
(“Radostak Paganetti”) have been compared with 
<taxonomicName box="[212,316,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vignai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[212,227,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[242,316,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">vignai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,392,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[324,392,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
It was found out that the aedeagus, left paramere and copulatory piece of both taxa are completely different. Besides, 
<taxonomicName box="[513,617,190,216]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vignai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[513,528,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[543,617,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">vignai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[625,692,190,216]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[625,692,190,216]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possesses the pronotum superficially but very clearly punctate close to lateral and basal margins as well as within and around the basal impressions, the lustre of tegument is stronger, and the pronotum scarcely wider than long, whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[897,1059,268,294]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dalmatinus">
<emphasis box="[897,912,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[927,1059,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">dalmatinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks punctures close to lateral and basal margins of pronotum and within and around the basal impressions, the lustre of tegument is weaker and the pronotum much wider than long. Most probably, 
<taxonomicName box="[828,990,345,371]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dalmatinus">
<emphasis box="[828,843,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[859,990,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">dalmatinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has to be removed from the checklist of the Italian fauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
